      <bioghist id="aspace_4af42bcd4dfe7012ac3c8736d6591ba8">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Thomas Walter Swan was born on December 20, 1877, in Norwich, Connecticut. He served as dean of the Yale Law School from 1916 to 1927, as a judge on the United States Circuit Court of Appeals, and as a member of the Yale Corporation. Swan died in New Haven, Connecticut, on July 15, 1975.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <arrangement id="aspace_b268588a8362cd34008b9108af0eca9f">
